Stack Navigations

1) We have to develop the screens to work the stack Navigations
2)We have to install the Packages

They are
    -> npx expo install react-native-screens react-native-safe-area-context
    -> npm install @react-navigation/native
    -> npm install @react-navigation/native-stack
    -> npm install @react-navigation/stack


 ** Structure to create Navigation **

*** Native-Stack-Navigation is the proper one to develop rather than stack-navigation *** 

<NavigationContainer>
    <Stack.Navigator
     screenOptions={{  //While styling of screen
        title: "Hai"  //for the title of the screen

        headerShown: false //for removing the nav bar

        headerStyle:{     //for stylings
            backgroundColor: "red"
        }

        headerTintColor: "red" //for header color

        headerTitleStyle:{  //height of the title  
            fontSize: 18
        }

        headerTitleAlign: "center"  //this is only for android For IOS it is default

        //For icon we have to import icon from react-native-paper
        headerRight:()=><Icon source={"Bell"} size={20} />
        headerLeft:()=><Icon source={"Home"} size={20} />  //it leans to disable back button and function


        headerBackButtonDisplayMode:"minimal" //It is to disable a ios back button name

        animation:"fade"  //they have pre defined animation while development


     }}
    >
        <Stack.Screen name="Home" component={Home} />
        <Stack.Screen name="Contact" component={Contact} />
    <Stack.Navigator>    
<NavigationContainer>


---> Sending data between screens
 We have to send from one screen to other by the use of Routes "useRoute"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Bottom Tab Navigation

1) We have to install the packages
    -> npm install @react-navigation/bottom-tabs
    -> npm install react-native-vector-icons  //Lets check the icons in the react-native-vector-icons

We have to import NavigationContainer form @react-navigation/native 
We have to import createBottomTabNavigator form @react-navigation/bottom-tabs

<NavigationContainer>
    <BottomTabNavigation.Navigator
        screenOptions={{

            tabBarActiveTintColor: "red", //for active color

            tabBarInactiveTintColor: "blue", //for inactive color

            tabBarLabelStyle:{fontSize: 15 , borderWidth: 1}, //for label styling

            tabBarIcon:({color,size})=><Icon source={"Home"} size={size} color={color} /> //for icons in the bottom navigation

            tabBarItemStyle:{backgroundColor: "red"} //for styling the bottom navigation

            tabBarStyle:{height: 60} //for styling the bottom navigation  
        }}

        screenOptions={({route})=>({  //for different icons in the bottom navigation
            tabBarIcon:({focused,color,size})=>{
                let iconName;
                if(route.name === "Home"){
                    iconName = focused ? "Home" : "home-outline"
                }else if(route.name === "Contact"){
                    iconName = focused ? "Contact" : "contact-outline"
                }
                return <Icon source={iconName} size={size} color={color} />
                tabBarActiveTintColor: "indigo", //for active color
                tabBarInactiveTintColor: "black", //for inactive color
            }
        })}
    >               //It will provide both the navigation.
        <BottomTabNavigation.Screen name="Home" component={Home} />
        <BottomTabNavigation.Screen name="Contact" component={Contact} />
    </BottomTabNavigation.Navigator>
</NavigationContainer>


For Home page we have to import useNavigation from @react-navigation/native and we have to use the navigation for the button to navigate to the contact page